caption.text: Having a journey in a day is tiring but really worthy. When you head north and you see your shadows on your left, you still got a lot of energy to go around, to go to new places and meet new peoples. Then you turn right, but now your shadows is only a tiny little dot at your feet, half energy is gone but the curiosity still there asking you to move further, the formula to go far is to go with less people, so you pick those who can support you. Then you go south, shadows on your left, the time to go home is coming soon. And now you're asking yourself "what  have I done? What should I bring home?"
